The horrific accident occurred on Groblesdal road just after Bronkhorstspruit, north of Gauteng earlier today."It is with sadness to inform that, a minibus transporting learners was involved in a horrific accident, and about 20 learners died on the scene," department of Education spokesman Steve Mabona said.Mabona said in a statement that &nbsp;MEC of Education Panyaza Lesufi was rushing to the scene.The department said more information will be shared in due course.@DBE_SA Minister Motshekga has just shared the sad news regarding the tragic accident involving learners in Bronkhortspruit. pic.twitter.com/tn32Izktm5&mdash; Elijah Mhlanga (@ElijahMhlanga) April 21, 2017@DBE_SA Minister Motshekga has conveyed her condolences to all the families affected as a result of the accident.&mdash; Elijah Mhlanga (@ElijahMhlanga) April 21, 2017@DBE_SA The Minister says the safety of learners is a priority. The use of bakkies and overloaded minibuses must stop.&mdash; Elijah Mhlanga (@ElijahMhlanga) April 21, 2017@DBE_SA Minister Motshekga says the cause of the accident is unknown at this stage. Gauteng Education MEC Lesufi is rushing to the scene.&mdash; Elijah Mhlanga (@ElijahMhlanga) April 21, 2017[UPDATE] - Fatalities on the R25 collision has risen to 17 children. @ewnupdates @eNCA @_ArriveAlive @JacaNews @SABCNewsroom pic.twitter.com/AumRsLrjFC&mdash; ER24 EMS (Pty) Ltd. (@ER24EMS) April 21, 2017[UPDATE] - The number of fatalities from the R25 collision has once again risen and confirmed at 20 children. @ewnupdates @eNCA @JacaNews&mdash; ER24 EMS (Pty) Ltd. (@ER24EMS) April 21, 2017[R25] - Taxi and truck collide leave approx 13 dead, several injured. https://t.co/PEyuvbGG8e @ewnupdates @eNCA @_ArriveAlive @JacaNews pic.twitter.com/bbqN4GU1aj&mdash; ER24 EMS (Pty) Ltd. (@ER24EMS) April 21, 2017